gh-dl is a client to download all public GitHub repositories from users and/or
organizations to create a compressed archive of the result.

./gh-gl [-f] [-l level] [-t duration] user...

The -l option specifies the gzip compression level 0 <= l <= 9. Default is
usually okay. The -t option specifies the timeout when cloning the git repo.

If the downloads are interrupted, it will leave a folder in the /tmp directory.

Example execution on the users "esote", "git", and "torvalds" with a 1s
timeout (meaning large repos are skipped).

	$ gh-dl -t 1s esote git torvalds
	using the working directory /tmp/gh-dl-042272538
	found 6 repositories for torvalds
	found 7 repositories for git
	found 30 repositories for esote
